## FEEDBACK to VERSION 0
here are some feedbacks:
The current result lists the analytical steps rather than presenting the extracted requirements and evaluation criteria in the requested JSON structure. The task asks to “Extract and structure key requirements and evaluation criteria from the job description,” so the output should directly reflect those extracted items.

here are the changes:
```json
{
  "required_skills": [
    /* List of technical and soft skills extracted, e.g., "JavaScript", "React", "problem-solving", "team collaboration" */
  ],
  "experience_level": "",  
    /* e.g., "3+ years software development", "Senior level" */
  "responsibilities": [
    /* Core duties, e.g., "Design and implement user interfaces", "Collaborate with cross-functional teams" */
  ],
  "certifications_and_qualifications": [
    /* e.g., "AWS Certified Solutions Architect", "Bachelor’s in Computer Science" */
  ],
  "technologies_and_tools": [
    /* e.g., "Node.js", "Docker", "Kubernetes" */
  ],
  "domain_expertise": [
    /* e.g., "E-commerce", "FinTech", "Healthcare systems" */
  ],
  "personality_and_cultural_fit": [
    /* e.g., "Proactive communicator", "Adaptable to agile environments" */
  ],
  "evaluation_criteria": [
    /* Criteria the interview or hiring team will use, e.g., "Coding test performance", "Peer review feedback", "System design challenge" */
  ],
  "performance_indicators": [
    /* KPIs mentioned or implied, e.g., "On-time feature delivery", "Bug resolution rate" */
  ],
  "requirement_priority": {
    "high": [
      /* Requirements emphasized most frequently or as critical */
    ],
    "medium": [
      /* Important but not critical */
    ],
    "low": [
      /* Nice-to-have or optional */
    ]
  }
}
```
